1. e4 b6 {The Owen's defense. Black prepares ...Bb7. He is willing to allow 
White a pawn center in order to obtain piece pressure against it. This approach 
is objectively unsound because White is able to safely consolidate his pawn 
center.} 2. d4 Bb7 3. Bd3 {[%cal Bg1f3,Bd1e2][%csl Gd4,Ge4] White supports his 
e4-pawn. It is worth delaying Nc3 because it is often useful to meet ...c5 with 
c3. White will likely follow up with Nf3 and Qe2, Black has insufficient 
compensation for White's pawn center.} *

